\'93The challenge facing data-rich literary history\'97of proposing a historically coherent whole (a literary system) from a collection or collections of parts (the disciplinary infrastructure and the digitized documents and literary data it transmits)\'97suggests the strategy for meeting it. The scholarly edition has long offered both a theoretical basis and a practical technology for demonstrating and managing the documentary record\'92s partiality. Applied to the literary system rather than the literary work, the scholarly edition provides a framework for investigating the history of transmission constitutive of the literary system modeled, justifying the selections and decisions made in that analysis, and publishing the outcomes.\'94 (Bode 52)\
\'93
\b The critical apparatus describes and justifies the editor\'92s engagement with the documentary record
\b0  constitutive of the literary work, including the inevitable gaps and uncertainties that engagement exposes and creates. 
\b The curated text represents the outcome of that extended critical encounter
\b0 , offering to those who accept its tenets\'97or who lack the expertise to engage with the documentary record in that manner\'97both an argument about the nature of the literary work and a foundation for analysis of that work.\'94 (Bode 53)\
\'93
\b Much more than simply describing the construction of a dataset\'97something already offered by many data-rich literary history projects
\b0 \'97this critical apparatus elaborates the complex relationships between the historical context explored, the disciplinary infrastructure employed in investigating that context, the decisions and selections implicated in creating and remediating the collection or collections, and the transformations wrought by the editor\'92s extraction, construction, and analysis of that data.\'94 (Bode 53)\
