\b A curated dataset replaces the curated text for a scholarly edition of a literary system
\b0 . In the form of bibliographical and textual data, it manifests\'97demonstrates and, specifically, publishes\'97the outcome of the sequence of production and reception, including the current moment of interpretation, described in the critical apparatus.\'94 (Bode 53)\
\'93The model it provides is stable: it is published and accessible for all to use, whether for conventional or computational literary history. But that stability does not belie or extinguish its hypothetical character. \'85 Its suitability and reliability for literary-historical research is established by a relationship between the historical phenomena and the data model that is explicitly interpretive and contingent rather than supposedly direct or natural.\'94 (Bode 53)\
